</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,487]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,344,370]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[686,933,345,371]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[686,811,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">V. fasciata</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be separated from the latter by tergites 
<number box="[251,298,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
with white recumbent scales antero-laterally and tergites 
<number box="[1025,1072,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
with white recumbent scales postero-laterally. In 
<taxonomicName box="[387,508,423,448]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[387,508,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">V. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tergites 
<number box="[616,631,422,448]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[687,702,422,448]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="3.0">3</number>
have yellowish recumbent scales antero-laterally, tergite 
<number box="[1375,1389,422,448]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="4.0">4</number>
has yellowish recumbent scales anteriorly, and tergites 
<number box="[750,793,461,487]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
have yellowish recumbent scales posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
